overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire application, aiming to elevate its visual appeal
  beyond a "generic" look. The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the existing
  CSS and component styling, identifying key areas for improvement in color,
  typography, layout, and form elements. The approach involved implementing a
  new, calming sleep-themed color palette, redesigning the main form layout with
  subtle decorative elements, and enhancing the welcome screen with feature
  cards and improved alerts. Crucially, all UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and progress bars were polished for a cohesive feel. The
  agent then systematically updated all 14 form sections to ensure consistent
  styling, replacing old gray boxes with refined cards and consistent headers.
  The report section also received a visual refresh. The agent used browser
  tools to verify the visual changes and performed lint checks to ensure code
  quality. The outcome is a significantly more polished, cohesive, and
  professional-looking application that aligns with a sleep health theme.
